`kodak_gold_200.png` is baked from spektrafilm's `kodak_gold_200` profile, by
Andrea Volpato (<https://github.com/andreavolpato/spektrafilm>). spektrafilm's
license treats a LUT as a direct encoding of its profile data, so the profile's
license comes with it — including the requirement that this notice travel with
every copy and every derivative.

This file does not restate, summarise or interpret that grant. An earlier
version of it did, and a summary of someone else's license is not their license:
it omitted terms they wrote deliberately, among them a trademark restriction on
the spektrafilm name, a request regarding commercial AI training, and the fact
that removing attribution terminates the grant outright.

  Verbatim upstream notice:  SPEKTRAFILM_LICENSE.txt (in this directory)
  CC BY-SA 4.0 legal code:   https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode
  Human-readable summary:    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

For what was changed in the bake, why this directory is a license carve-out, and
Film Lab's own reading of what share-alike does and does not reach, see
ATTRIBUTION.md. That reading is Film Lab's, and is not part of anyone else's
license grant.
